Emoni, who was expelled from the Adventurer's Guild, relied
on the connections she had with nobles and the Senate.

Many influential individuals feared opposing the
Adventurer's Guild, and while there were some who provided
minimal support, that was all.

In the midst of such days, Emoni reminded herself that she
couldn't afford the pathetic act of returning to her family,
thinking of her capable father and talented brothers.

And above all, there was a determination towards Guild
Master Agonia. Unconsciously, Emoni saw her father's figure
in Agonia. It was a desire to be recognized amidst the mixed
feelings of love and hate.

In the midst of her frustrating days, Emoni was introduced
to a job as a royal court official by a powerful noble. She
saw this as the perfect opportunity and immediately jumped
at it. She believed that this would allow her to prove
herself to everyone, that was what she thought.

At that time, Emoni had forgotten the advice of Agonia and
her father. Don't act recklessly. Emoni would end up working
under the worst person imaginable.
